      m_Calls: []
  m_text: 'The simplest projection is the one-dimensional, wherein the quantity is
    represented with an arrow pointing to a specific direction, usually in one of
    the four cardinal directions (NESW). The two- dimensional projection shows the
    vector value represented by an arrow pointing in a direction specified by two
    (2) components: the x- and y-axes, which is measured by an angle. The complex
    form of projection, the three-dimensional, represents the vector with an arrow
    that uses three components: x, y, and the z-axis.'
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: ed9fe41215e4a2c4a9fa581443855244, type: 2}
